name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Nice market place right next to water. Season fruits and veggies (strawberry, lingonberry, mushrooms….). It’s funny because all of them have exactly the same products, we need to make a choice then!
Departure of small boats there.
We can just sit in the area and look at the cruise ship leaving the port and at the cathedral on the top a the hill.
Parking zone 1 same price than the rest of the whole area center.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Feels like the centre of Helsinki. Lovely square, with aggressive seagulls. Young people singing songs on repeat and a wide range of food for the seagulls to pounce on, keep your wits about you. Boat trips around the archipelago well worth the money to have a couple of drinks as you see the various islands and get a bit of history.
Pleasant place for lunch and a couple of hours listening to people singing three little birds... more than once.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: A really nice place to have a chill lunch by the harbour. lots of stalls with food and trinkets. slightly overpriced for the portions but food tasted great!

name: Kauppatori
review_text: I had the pleasure of visiting Helsinki for the first time recently, and I was thoroughly impressed by the market square. There was an abundance of delicious foods to sample, interesting items to purchase, and opportunities to create lasting memories of my visit to Helsinki. I highly recommend a visit to the market, and I look forward to returning to this wonderful place on my next trip to Helsinki.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: A really great and delicious Salmon Soup and Iced Coffee at Story Cafe. Bought a lot of local delicacies from the other stalls too. Worth to visit, rather than blindly buying Salmon Soup at the outside stalls

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Nice market, mixture of fresh produce, locally made food / items and tourist tat. Pretty expensive as you would imagine. Great views of the harbour area, and plenty of little market stalls with drinks and snacks.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
I loved this place! It’s a medium Sized market with lots of restaurants to eat
Local food (like salmon soup and skagen toast), you can also buy lots of food to go and typical finish delicatessen like reindeer ham and some pastries. We recommend checking the schedule as we wanted to come back to eat the next day and it was closed, also bring money as there are lots to buy and try. The market is super well located with lots of places to view around and you can also just sit outside and enjoy the view!

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Summer months only but a vibrant mixed market with food and handmade craft produce, as well as the usual tourist tat.  Really nice place with friendly stall holders.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Cool spot if you’re into local vibes with a side of touristy flair. You’ll find fresh berries, fish, and plenty of souvenirs—some of it pricey, but that’s what you get in a market like this. The real draw? The food stalls. Grab some salmon soup or reindeer sausage, and eat while watching ferries and dodging aggressive seagulls. It's a bit chaotic, but that’s part of the charm.

Good for a quick stroll, just don’t expect it to be cheap.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Beyond gorgeous in summer time, the sea is beautiful, the outdoor market has a variety of seasonal fruits and vegetables, the vendace (small fish) is a must-have and it's easy to find. You can try some grilled salmon. Of course it's more than just the food and gorgeous view, you can take a dinner or sightseeing cruise, and jump to Suomenlinna for an incredible visit to a UNESCO world heritage site. You can also go to the old market hall and admire the beauty, explore the offerings of Finnish cuisine, have some oysters and wine or have some salmon soup, or even just grab some beer and enjoy!

name: Kauppatori
review_text: This is the perfect place for tourists. Very vibrant and the heart of Helsinki. You will get many handicrafts and souvenir shop here. Also there is have so many restaurants where you can taste the local food along with the international. Also have some fruit and fresh vegetable stall. Its a small port for boat and surrounding by historical landmark. Helsinki boat trip depart from here. Highly recommended this place.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Good place to visit and try local cuisine.
A year-round harbor market with food and handicraft stalls and a café in a tent heated in winter.
Many souvenirs, food, and local stuff

name: Kauppatori
review_text: A must place to be when you visit Helsinki. First try something at the local food ... The salmon was also the small fried fish . And the "rudolf" the reindeer sausage !!!.. i taste them all and find them very tasty ! Second there is a good market for souvenirs in good price , third you can take some beautiful pictures of the harbour and picture the only building with the Finnish flag !! ( Next to the Sweden's) .., and just search why you don't see any Finnish flags nowhere else at the city???? ( I give you that as a trivia !!!l)

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Perfect spot as a tourist to find all kinds of souvenirs and handcrafted finnish things!

Food and fruits they sell taste amazing!! I recommend the strawberries 🍓!!

(My wife made me buy half the market)

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Lots of stalls but many of them sell the same, or very similar, items. Food stalls are pretty much all the same, as are vegetable stalls. Still, there are a few handicraft stalls that sell unique items. Watch out for seagulls if you’re buying food! They’ll snap it out your hand!!

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Location where you can take the ferry to Suomenlinna.
There is sauna and swimming pool close by.
We had some salmon dishes: salmon plate and salmon soup.
The fruits sold there are good quality.
You can buy some souvenirs too.
Be aware of the many birds which try to steal your food.
There is one water source where you can fill your empty bottle with fresh water.
It's about 15 minutes walking from Helsinki Railway station. Nice walking.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Helsinki Market Square is a vibrant waterfront marketplace offering fresh produce, handicrafts, and local delicacies. With its lively atmosphere, historic landmarks, and convenient ferry access to nearby islands. You can also buy exotic meats here.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: The market square is a good location to start your visit. Close to the old market hall, short walk to the Senate square and you can board the ferry to islands here. Usually there are the orange market stalls. A lot will sell salmon soup or traditional dishes such as reindeer with mash.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Open market. Street Food and Craft store. One must try here there salmon stew and fried Firefish with Garlic Sauce.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Nice area to walk and see different stores. A lot of historical buildings around. You can also eat at different restaurants.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Cute little market but we visited during the week so it was not very busy. The outside portion of the central market was great, we bought a few things but it was very cold out so not many tents were open. But it was nice to walk along the Baltic Sea (Gulf of Finland) while browsing locally made items.-2016

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Glad I came here, the street food is amazingly delicious! I ordered the salmon, fried fish and veggies.  And a great beer to accompany it   you will enjoy it.  The location is close to the ferry and other touristy sites. There was a protest that day, a nicely organized event,

name: Kauppatori
review_text: A delightful place at the central place in beautiful city of Helsinki .Very enjoyble during summer time . Plenty of food kiosks , sitting places around to enjoy the magnified views see there .

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Very close to central Helsinki. A cute food Hall but it has very interesting restaurants. Many traditional Finnish restaurants as well as a Vietnamese soup restaurant. They close at 6 pm, this place is not ideal for dinner.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Nice place to stroll around.  Done great market stalks selling goods and yummy food . Also can sit and relax and look.at the ships

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Great old style market in front of the president palace. Offers lots of great classic Finnish food like salmon platter, vandace fish, reindeer dish with very generous sized portion. Highly recommended

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
So many options, but do not miss the fish platters!
So tasty, easily fits 2 people.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Nice place to eat and buy various souvenirs. The salmon and prawns were delicious and well seasoned. The stands accept card. Be careful of the birds trying to take your food though!

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Good food, great place, lots of Finnish souvenirs to choose and buy. Beautiful scenery of the pier.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Perhaps here you can see the truely helsinki, where the hawkers sell local foods and fruits also the merchandise about finland. A bịt busy with tourists but worth visiting and sightseeing boat trips is started here.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Helsinki’s Market Square, locally known as Kauppatori, stands as a vibrant testament to Finnish culture and daily life. Nestled by the waterfront in the heart of Helsinki, it’s a must-visit for both locals and tourists. Here’s an in-depth look at what makes this iconic spot so special and tips on making the most of your visit.

1. Location and Atmosphere

Located at the southern end of Esplanadi and adjacent to the Presidential Palace, Kauppatori offers stunning views of the Baltic Sea and Helsinki’s harbor. The square is alive with a flurry of activities, from vendors setting up stalls to ferries departing for Suomenlinna. The atmosphere is lively and authentic, with the smell of fresh fish and baked goods filling the air, and the sounds of seagulls mingling with the chatter of shoppers.

2. A Feast for the Senses

Culinary Delights: One of Kauppatori’s main draws is its diverse range of food offerings. Seafood lovers will find an array of freshly caught fish and shellfish. Highlights include the salmon soup, a Finnish classic, and the herring dishes that come in a variety of preparations. For a quick snack, try the market’s renowned fried vendace (muikku), served with garlic sauce. Don’t miss out on local pastries like the traditional Finnish cinnamon roll (korvapuusti) or the seasonal berries, which are both delicious and fresh.

Handicrafts and Souvenirs: Beyond food, the square is also a treasure trove of Finnish handicrafts and souvenirs. You’ll find stalls selling handmade woolen products, traditional knives, jewelry, and various items featuring Moomins, the beloved Finnish characters. These make for great keepsakes or gifts.

3. Seasonal Highlights

Kauppatori is especially captivating during the warmer months. In summer, the square hosts the Helsinki Herring Market (Silakkamarkkinat) and various festivals. The long summer days also make it a perfect time to enjoy an alfresco meal at one of the outdoor cafés, with a glass of Finnish beer or berry juice.

Winter brings a different charm, with the market transforming into a winter wonderland. Seasonal delicacies like reindeer meat and mulled wine (glögi) become the highlights. The Christmas Market features beautifully decorated stalls and is a wonderful place to soak up the festive spirit.

4. Accessibility and Tips

Getting There: The market is easily accessible by public transportation. It’s a short walk from the Helsinki Central Railway Station, and several tram lines stop nearby. For those driving, parking can be a bit challenging, so it’s advisable to use public transit or explore on foot.

Best Time to Visit: Mornings are ideal for those who want to experience the market at its most authentic, as vendors are setting up and the crowds are smaller. If you prefer a more leisurely pace, late afternoons provide a relaxed atmosphere, though some stalls may begin to close.

Exploration Tips:

•	Ferry to Suomenlinna: Combine your visit with a ferry trip to the nearby Suomenlinna Sea Fortress, a UNESCO World Heritage site.
•	Photography: The waterfront offers excellent opportunities for photography, especially during sunrise or sunset.
•	Interaction: Don’t hesitate to chat with the vendors. Many speak English and can offer insights into Finnish culture and products.

5. Practical Information

Opening Hours: The market operates year-round, but hours vary by season. Typically, it opens from 8 AM to 6 PM on weekdays and has shorter hours on weekends. The winter months may see reduced activity due to the cold.

Facilities: Public restrooms are available, and many stalls accept credit cards, although it’s wise to carry some cash for smaller purchases. The area is generally stroller and wheelchair-friendly, though it can get crowded during peak times.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: There are many shops selling food such as salmon, mui kugui, and stir-fried sausages and potatoes, as well as souvenirs at Market Square.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: What a beautiful city in a beautiful country! So much to see, eat, and do. Great public transportation on clean and modern trains and trolleys, and a very nice airport. A wonderful family destination for sure! 😊

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
This is a very touristy area but still lots of fun. There are plenty of vendors.

This is a good place to buy useful and wearable souvenirs (as well as junk souvenirs). There are also lots of food vendors, each with plenty of seating. The fish items are very tasty. The reindeer hotdog, so I’ve been told, is not.

From here, you are steps away from Senate Square, Uspenski Catheral, and dining spots near the terminal.

A must stop place for any Helsinki visitor.

Special shout out to the Ape Gelato truck. That is the cutest and most amazing design for a food truck. I want that truck!!  ❤️ ❤️ ❤️

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Great food and generous portions. As my my first meal in Finland, I felt very welcomed.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: It was a delightful walking tour experiencing Helsinki and getting to know more about Finland history. Applaud to our red umbrella walking guide Matti who is really energised, knowledgeable and funny. Enjoyed it.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Food and craft market
Located at the pier
Good selection and open all year round

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Helsinki is a compact city. One can explore major tourist places by walking.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: A touristy food market with fresh produce, souvenirs and Finnish delicacies. You cannot access Suomenlinna boats through the market.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Just opposite City Hall is the market square with amazing local markets and shop to get local food / fruits and cafe to buy.

Multiple shops with souvenir and ice creams. It's a must visit while u staying..I loved feeding sea gulls here 👌

Suggestion : this is a common point you need to arrive to do Ferris wheel /city sightseeing cruise or ferry for soumelina islands. So keep some buffet ad arrive 1 hour early. So same day u can see market place and do excursions. Toilets in city hall are free if required to use

name: Kauppatori
review_text: We were impressed with the street food in Helsinki. Delicious Salmon. Highly recommended.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: A nice place. There are some stalls with gifts, food, and fruit. Fruit is still expensive and the selection is very limited.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Great touristic attraction in Helsinki - Finland. A must visit place. Check pics

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Do not fall from the stalls and stands. Usually you can find the same kinds of merchandise in actual markers for a significantly lower price. Go here for the ambience and the experience of going so Suomenlinna for a nice walk around the island.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Great stop to view the harbor at Helsinki. Great place to buy souvenirs from local vendors.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Delicious food and friendly service where we ate. Not fancy at all though. Tents that they remove each Wednesday morning to clean apparently and put back the same day.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: One place for all your shopping in Helsinki. Lots of food stalls serving the authentic salmon soup. It’s just at the ferry point for Suomelinna. So you get your food with a sea view as well.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Lots of typical Finnish food choices, places to eat and rest near the sea and watch ferries.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: A typical food market that can be seen in Eurupean countries. You cab find local foods and goods inside. There are many closed stands inside but still good to visit if you have enough time in Helsinki.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
I totally recommend to visit this place and try some local dishes and buy local hand-crafted things. I went in winter so not many tents where open.
This is where you go to take the boats to Soumelina island. The indoor market is just around the corner.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Fantastic market offering a delightful array of local cuisine, with a particular emphasis on delectable salmon dishes. While I cannot personally compare it to its past state, I must say that it has become quite popular among tourists. Nevertheless, the market retains its charm and provides an excellent opportunity to savor authentic flavors and browse for unique souvenirs.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: There is this booth past the food section where you can get the magnets at the cheapest rate in Helsinki! Even the original Moomin magnets are way  cheaper than the Moomin Stores (5 euros per magnet with no discout at the official stores). I recommend this place to all!

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
One of the most touristic parts of the city. At the end of the Esplanadi steet there is this square full of market tents. The view is beautiful on the harbours and from there you can go sightseeing boat tours.
Here you will have many options to try famous typical Finnish food, such as salmon soup, smoked salmon or raindeer.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: This is an open bazaar where you can find a variety of food and souvenirs. It's a typical place to enjoy seafood and fast food options. Although I didn't try the food myself, it seems like a nice place to spend time and enjoy the fresh air.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Interesting outdoor market a little over the top but the Helsinki City Hall, Swedish Embassy and Finish Presidential Palace all across the street was quite enjoyable.  We ate here as well, a bot challenging and bought a few things to bring home.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Great place, just get a viking line ship & get into the tour.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Good starting place for tourists to get some berries, licorice ice cream, local delicacies and drinks and eat by the marina. Beware of seagulls who can snatch away your food. You can also get some non-food items and crafts items here.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
You can enjoy the Finnish style fried fish here. They are so yummy!
But the whole price is going up!
Everything costs more, but still it's fun place to walk around and eat!

name: Kauppatori
review_text: We tried the salmon soup and salmon .Although stalls all sell the same they were sold out of the soup and reindeer meat. The food was good but the prices as imagined in Finland were very pricey, 4Euros for a can of coke! Stalls selling similar items some handmade nice ones rest tourist tat.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Really neat place to walk around, have a bite to eat and enjoy the view.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: It presents a selection of fish specialties that beautifully display the legacy of the city. From caught salmon to herring creations, the fish options are a true delight for seafood lovers. The skilled chefs expertly craft these dishes, maintaining the flavors and textures that embody Finlands customs.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: An open air market place with stalls selling a variety of food and souvenirs, this is one location that you should visit in Helsinki when the weather is good. While it's not the main market place, it's still quite authentic and local. You can order food and sit in the different stalls to enjoy the scenery of the harbour and ships coming in and out. The food are quite good too and worth it. Highly recommended.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
A nice small market across the road from the presidents palace located on the city wharf.
Many stalls, some selling souvenirs and clothes but most are food stalls serving fried/baked fish of all sorts as well as tinned and marinated fish pieces in jars.
There is one Tacos stand number 26 which I bought some Tacos from. Very nice and fresh food and something different to eat. The staff were friendly and made my food with care.
A nice little market and great Tacos!

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
A lovely square filled with bars and restaurants and surrounded by beautiful buildings.
There's plenty of platforms for sitting in the middle of the square, and even a few hanging chairs, if you're lucky enough to find an empty one.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Here you can find traditional tasty dishes and souvenirs. Prices are lower than inside the market building. Don't forget to take a hat or hoody, the wind might be uncomfortable.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Wonderful food and shopping options and boats to nearby islands

name: Kauppatori
review_text: A very nice experience. A lovely market vibe, relaxed & upbeat. Wonderful architecture surrounding the market area. The views out over the harbour are just great, watching the giant cruise ships coming & going. We'll be going back to Helsinki one day😀

name: Kauppatori
review_text: lots of shops with souvenirs and food! shared some yummy salmon with my mom here today for lunch…delicious!

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Food, clothes, souvenirs. This market has many stalls inside and outside. Something for everyone. A nice place to walk around or have a bite to eat. Plenty to choose from.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Local street market which gives you the opportunity to taste local dishes in decent prices in addition to really high prices in restaurants etc.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
A bit touristy perhaps, but always worth a visit!

I tried the salmon plate here at one of the stalls and found it to be quite tasty and a generous portion. That said, to charge €8 for a 'large beer' - only to later discover it was an alcohol lite beer of only 2.8%, made me feel a little cheated. Perhaps I should have reviewed the can before buying it though! Something to keep in mind.

Just also be aware that there's a lot of wasps flying around the market during warm days and if you're like me and loathe the things, this may not be the best place to eat outside!

That said, I do recommend this food market!

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Open market, in sunny weather it was very nice. Good range of foods, fresh produce too. As a vegetarian i did not find much and the smell or cooking was overwhelming at times. The seagulls are a definite menace.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Very strategic location in Helsinki to taste local dishes and to purchase locally made handicrafts.

It’s a cool place to stop for a snack or a drink if you are sightseeing and need a quick break.

Also, the building and the surrounding areas are very scenic and rich in history.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: One of the places that you need to visit when you are in Helsinki. There are many food stalls and souvenirs. I tried one of the stalls named Sun Market Finland, and ordered their Salmon Soup. The soup tastes good, the taste of the salmon is strong and the rye bread is a good compliment for this dish.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: You can take your food and eat it while sitting by the sea.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: A great outdoor market, well worth a visit. Lots of handmade crafts, local souvenirs as delicious street food including local specialties unique to the region.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Incredibly tasty local food! Must try if you’re visiting the city. Salmon is rich and perfectly cooked, vendace is insanely good. Interesting options with Moose and Reindeer

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
In a Tuesday in February at 12 there we’re almost no stalls. Maybe ten in total. However we found a good stall which served us amazing fish dishes in nice atmosphere even though weather was pretty bad. We were also able to taste dishes before ordering them as we never had this food before.
Price for a big portion was about 14€, portion served two people.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: It’s ok. Product is a little pricier than the supermarket but they are great if you’re picking up some snacks as you’re headed out. Getting any hot food does mean you might be attack by seagull, so watch out for that. It’s nice to walk by and take a look, but I wouldn’t plan a stop here as part of your time in Helsinki.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Very delicious food. I enjoyed the salmon soup, fresh strawberries/blueberries and I also had their reindeer hot dog. You have to try it. That’s all I will say about it . Went for a walk with my girlfriend in the marketplace and I enjoyed everything. This was my first time. Will definitely come back

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Lovely open-market to walk around

name: Kauppatori
review_text: From food, to fruit and souvenirs, you find it all. Quite an unique place, the tents could look better. Just be mindful of the seagulls

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Even when the weather is warm, the Finns are chilled. It's easy to use the market square as your start and end point for a walking tour of Helsinki and you can even see some of the landmarks from the square.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: This is a pretty good spot. Sunday was less busy. Monday was better, more shops, more food choices, etc. the food was pretty good! And lots of choices. The seagulls are VERY aggressive, so keep your food safe! The shops are cool, but a decent amount of replication in offerings. Nothing to write home about as far as an amazing shopping or eating area. Lots of cruise people walking around, seems mostly geared for them.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Incredible little market with a great selection of wares and amazing Street food. Probably the healthiest Street food in the world with salmon, potato and vegetables available as well as out of the norm stuff like reindeer hot dogs. We had the Salmon and it was some of the best fish I have ever eaten, definitely a recommendation from me.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: This is an old, covered fish and food market in Helsinki. I had read before that the food here is good and reasonably priced. However, I found it to be expensive and didn’t end up eating anything.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Good place to taste Finnish food or enjoy coffee with  pulla. Fresh produce and souvenir shops. Or pick a nice cruise to the archipelago .

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Numerous street food and artisan outlets overlooking the beautiful harbour make this a very pleasant experience.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Really nice and warm place to check local food.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: One of my favourite markets and I visit it every time I go to Helsinki. It's not too big and it's a great location on a sunny day. I love people watching over coffee and the food stalls are great with a really appetising array of freshly cooked foods. Love it.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: What has happened to one of the central attractions of Helsinki? I hadn't visited Helsinki Market Square for many many years - and now, as I happened to visit there, it looked out like streets of North Korea. Where are all people? Where are all tourists? It was a beautiful warm summer morning at 9 or 10 o'clock, and alleys between small market shops where almost empty. Market places everywhere are places where to feel the local atmosphere, to see local culture, or at least to see tourists and local people selling their stuff to tourists. But Helsinki Market Square, what a dissappointment!

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Helsinki Market Square was alive pretty early when we arrived. There were several vendors available with (supposedly) local wares and crafts. There were some pretty cool finds, like reindeer Antler items, and leather goods. The vendors are really friendly. You can also access the boat tours from this location. We had some interesting reindeer hot dogs here from one of the vendors and also bought a few souvenirs. If you decide to get the vendace, watch out for the sea gulls as they will likely try to take it from you. The prices are insane, which would be my only complaint. I suspect this isn't the fault of the market, but more likely a tax issuee. All in all, I think it's worth a visit.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Best street food with great atmosphere in the harbour.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Market hall with various local food and some international options at the waterfront. Ate at a restaurant located near the centre to try their open shrimp sandwich and salmon soup. Both were delicious. Staff friendly and as with most places had an English menu and spoke English well. There's also a coffee place at the centre of the food hall. Otherwise pastries, cured meats, various types of honey, etc were also available. Certainly worth a visit and close to other famous Helsinki sights.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Wonderful fresh fruit and freshly made hot meals in a stunning seaside location. It is met down by surprisingly high prices and a lack of flexibility I.e. if you want a bunch of reindeer meatballs and not a dish with veg and other items, tough luck.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Some tents selling fruit, vegetables and knick-knacks. Some tents selling hot food for seagulls, which humans can also buy ;) Traders hawking sea cruises. And, the terminal for ferries to the interesting island of Suomelinna; payments by physical cards and Euro notes are possible on site; the coin slots are sometimes blocked, it seems.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Pretty in a beautiful day.  There is another part that is indoor which we did not see.  Quaint places to have fish soup by the water while waiting for our ferry to Suomenlinna.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: This is very Finnish. If you would like to try what you think are traditional Finnish dishes, you should visit this market. They offer delicacies such as vendace, reindeer meat, and moose burgers, among others. The food is absolutely delicious! Moreover, the market is located by the harbor, offering a beautiful view.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Got moose meatballs and Reindeer hot dog for 16 euro really dissapointing, very bland no herbs and spices, your better off trying food from the indoor market, this is a tourist trap. This food is under orange tents at the harbour for the boat excursions.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
All the fruit stalls are the same, clear increased tourist price, small portion of strawberries 7 to 8 euros
Ther strawberries were not packaged properly, they were all crushed into juice because they forgot to put on a lid and package them properly

It's best to eat them directly or let them pack them properly

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Try to somon soup!! Yummy and otontic place which take place in the sea-side

name: Kauppatori
review_text: The market square is where you will get a good cup of coffee and a snack. If you go for the other Finnish delicacies then expect to pay the price. The food is good for sure but for what you are getting and the seating etc, I just feel it’s over priced, but maybe it’s all part of the experience. Some souvenirs and other nicknacks on sale as well. I always enjoy a walk around the market when there and a cup of coffee.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: This is a crowded area (in the Scandinavian sense) with lots of tourists. Many activities going on. Taking hop on, sight seeing, fast food, selling souvenir etc. the food was amazing, especially the sea food fries.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Lovely place to stop for souvenirs and gift items made in Finland. Also, great fresh fruit and vegetable stands.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: The market square boasts all local produce. I bought some fresh, delicious berries and some souvenirs. The fish soup was particularly bland and unimpressive for my Indian palate. The ferry to Suomenlinna starts here

name: Kauppatori
review_text: One of the best local street markets ever. Exceptional high-end handmade products from Finland. The food is incredible, and it exudes summer vibes. ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
If you want salmon soup, herrings or anything in between, you are in the right place. Filled with as many people as seagulls, so when ordering the excellent food, be aware of the "attacking" seagulls, who try to steal your food from your hand.

It is so good that Seagulls try to steal it

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Very famous market selling traditional foods, souvenirs etc, loved the grilled salmon and Herring (do try it out!!). Also the location where you take the ferry to Suomenlinna fortress island, where the Helsinki eye is located, cinema 4d and hop on/off bus tour and cruises... Also an Awesome place to venture at night.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Small market place with food and gift vendors. It is also the  right next to where you take the ferry to Suomenlinna island and also the boat tours around the archipelago.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Beware of seagulls, hahaha. They love fish as much as you do

name: Kauppatori
review_text: A really great market right next to the sea. Prices are a bit high, but the place is nice. You can buy a lot of stuff here.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: A tourist trap, but still go here every year when i pass by Helsinfors to have my fish meal, coffee and a donut with a quick look at some stands. Nice place, good vibes and outrageous prices.. :-)

name: Kauppatori
review_text: A must go in Helsinki during all seasons. Especially great in the summer and during the herring market season. Make sure you taste a meat pie from "Torin Pojat". Some other stands also sell meat pies but the ones from legendary Torin Pojat are just simply the best and they also have a heated tent during the winter.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Friendly people, good food, spacialy little fried fish 🐟 good view 👌

name: Kauppatori
review_text: I am vegan so there is a strong smell of fish and meat all over. Besides that, its a place to shop for souvenirs

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Market with small stands , each of them it's own delicious meal to offer. All kind of sweet things, there are stands for meat lovers , for vegetarians, you will souveniers and drinks as well.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: The market square is vibrant. Interesting stalls and food outlets. Friendly people and pleasant atmosphere.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Fun market with a variety of cooked foods, raw fish, pastries and other sweets.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Great food stalls

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Really hard to come if you use your own car. 25€/3h parking... Nice place to take a ferry around islands and some Finnish merchandise. Would prefer lower prices...

name: Kauppatori
review_text: My brother, boyfriend and I got some food at one of the stands. My brother and I got some reindeer sausage with some veggies and it was simply not good. The alleged sausage ended up being a wiener instead. And the veggies would have been nice if only they weren’t completely covered in dill. It wasn’t like a little bit of it, you know. No, there was so much dill that I couldn’t taste a single vegetable, but rather felt like eating only dill itself. Also, we got this IPA beer, the only they had to offer (which was 7€) and it was simply terrible.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Fun & beautiful place! Lovely souvenirs, jewelry, clothes, and handmade items. Amazing food!! This marketplace smells sooo good.
We got a salmon plate and it was delicious! 🤤🍣🤤🇫🇮

name: Kauppatori
author_title: A H M E D Q
review_text:
Great area for buying hand made souvenirs, and having a fresh street food.

Try the Salmon platter with the potato and vegetables (Good portion).
It costs 19.5 Euros

name: Kauppatori
review_text: The glistening of the cobblestones is light enough to trick you into a bygone era. Or else almost enough. I love this market place. The stalls and the chatter as tourists catch a ferry or search out a meal. A beautiful centre of the city and a place I found myself drawn to again and again while in Helsinki.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Pretty cool place in the middle of center 😊there are a lot of places where we can buy typical souvenirs from Finland 🤩 from the pier there is a ferryboat to Suomelinna (for free if you have f.e.a day ticket). Few tents with food - recommended especially small fried fishes 🙆‍♀️🤪

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
There's lots of things to see, try, eat, and buy at this market! Especially in the summer, it is packed with people and lots of many tourists.
We had some salmon soup and a reindeer hotdog - and we were very happy with the food, it was delicious!

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
This was probably the worst food I've had, the salad was absolutely ruined with insane amounts of dill. The beer was awful.
I have no idea how this place has 4.3 stars, people clearly eat garbage at home.
If you respect your stomach, skip this place.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Place that sells local sovenirs and traditional finniah food
Try the salmon creamy soup!

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Definitely a tourist trap of sorts. The souvenirs are worth a look at to see whether you’d like to bring anything back. Found the food to be quite expensive for what it was. You’d probably be better off dining at a local restaurant as opposed to getting the street food (boggles the mind that you can charge €18++ for a small meal at a market). The food is pretty similar across the stores, serving up items such as open sandwiches, fried fish, hot dogs, etc. You could consider stopping if you’d like a quick bite but I wouldn’t expect anything mind blowing.

The lady at one of the stalls we visited was lovely / very friendly, with that being said. She let us try two small pieces of the fried fish as we were hesitant on getting a bigger portion without knowing what it tasted like.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Local food and craft. Prices might seem high, bot for reindeer / bear / elk meat they are simillar to sypermarket canned meat. Fish soup is a must to try.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Surprisingly, the postcards here are sold at affordable prices(1€) making it convenient to purchase souvenirs. However, the food offerings are rather ordinary, so it might be worth trying just for the experience.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Helsinki is a gorgeous city, interesting market stalls, great walking city. The people are gentle and welcoming, The architecture is extraordinary and walking through the streets feels like you are walking through an art gallery.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: loved the market Square. It's centered in the middle of some great attractions. It's on the water so you can sit and watch the ships. The Square on Friday is a very nice flea market..shopping for everyone. The food market is at the end of the pier , stop in and try some local food.  Saturday is for the travelers who love trying new food. There is food lined up on both sides..something for everyone. Overall The Square is a MUST VISIT for every who visits Helsinki.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: An interesting place for tourists

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Lots of lovely market stalls selling everything from food to hats and various trinkets. Be very careful of the seagulls here as they are watching people getting food and waiting to steal it from the unsuspecting person. It is  actually quite funny to watch.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Beautiful location and great variety of stalls.
Had a coffee at Cafe Caramelle before heading for a day trip to the most beautiful island in Helsinki - Vallisaari

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Among the very best open air markets in the whole of Europe.  Centrally located on downtown Helsinki shore at the eastern end of the main park boulevard Esplanadi.  Fresh quality produce, wool garments, wooden items, you name it...  Fun location for shopping and eating freshly cooked local fish in field restaurants.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Nice little fish market located between the square and the harbour. You can buy fresh catch directly from the fishermen boats or, on a rainy day inside the indoor market. Here you’ll find restaurants and cafes where to sit and enjoy some traditional smoked fish or meat on bread.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Nice market where you can find a lot of different things.
On the one hand there are a lot of different kinds of food available. You can have fresh fruits, fish, traditional food from Finnland and all kind of fast food. On the other hand there are a lot of handcrafted pieces available as well as the standard souvenirs.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Stopped for a obligatory portion of fried vendace, which turned out to be amazing, especially with the dill sauce. Watch out for seagulls around and find a sheltered spot in one of the tented areas, otherwise risk your potrtion to be stolen in an instant 😂

name: Kauppatori
review_text: If you want to try authentic local food and beer, this is the place. A lot of local people eat there, not only tourists.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Althought a little bit a tourist hotsport and must visit in Helsinki, still lovely place to have street food fish and take a ferry to surrounding island to Helsinki.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: A place not to be missed while in Helsinki.  Lots of booths with different sea food specials.  Beware of the flying sea eagles, they are really hungry 🙂

name: Kauppatori
review_text: A traditional food market. Very beautiful fishes in some of the stand. We enjoyed the traditional finish salmon soup in the main cafe that was indeed delicious. Honestly could have a better signal area to show the market as I almost missed walking by.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Nice place to find local cuisine and easy to get to white church complex

name: Kauppatori
review_text: This was a fun place to visit , got to eat traditional Finnish food here and buy souvenirs . Close to Helsinki cathedral , uspenski , and boat to Suomenlinna islands !

name: Kauppatori
review_text: The market square in Helsinki is a great place to take tours to different locations and it is good to take a snack or have lunch. It is a center point must see for sure.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Beautiful open air market at Christmas time . Just by the Senate and the cathedral . No way you could not happen to go here 😅

name: Kauppatori
review_text: A Classic market where you can buy nice stuff and eat, nice typical food🥰

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Beautiful hall with excellent architecture and they have made sure to not over commercialize it despite of it's large no of tourist visitors. Great place to get your breakfast or lunch fix and if you like salmon, you will LOVE this hall. Walk around and then nibble at a few places. Definitely should be in your list of places to visit in Helsinki

name: Kauppatori
review_text: It is an excellent location in the neighborhood, nothing like what one would experience in Milwaukee, WI. They have everything from produce to alcohol and everything in between. Unless you are looking for something special, you could make this your primary destination for grocery shopping. The staff is accommodating, and the location is well-stocked and maintained. I highly recommend you come to check it out if you need food supplies and are in the area!

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
A building with rich history and a good place to have a hearty local meal. Lots of stalls selling food, souvenirs, gifts at a reasonable price.

Would recommend this as a checkpoint for a short visit when exploring central Helsinki. You can also take a boat to Suomenlinna sea fortress as well for sightseeing.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Make sure to taste the seafood here I had a huge platter of salmon with vegetables and it was absolutely delicious.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
It’s a central square located on the eastern side of central Helsinki, between the south harbour and Esplanade Park.

There you can find some tends selling local food and souvenirs.

The food looks nice but it’s a bit pricey!

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Is a must visit area in Helsinki city centre with lots of small vendors selling traditional Finnish items and food, pastries etc. On a sunny day it can be crowded with locals and tourists. You can take also boat rides to different islands specially to Suomenlinna

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Tasty Finlandic regional food and traditional things can bay by the tourists. Starting places for the Sight Seeing Boot tours.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Nice little marketplace to be eat. Prices are great compared to restaurants. More like a place to fill your stomach... There's a similar concept as well in the new market area. Both re well enough (and close enough) to walk to

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Market Square is on the harbour area not far from center, walking distance. Here you can find lots of local produce likes berries, vegetables , meat etc. The are few people who are selling nice snack , soups and coffees too. You can easily explore the market before boarding to local boats for Simolienna island or going to Tallin.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
I love this place, especially in the early and sunny morning...

Every day you can find here plenty of original Finnish souvenirs and try traditional local food and  fast-food.

From here you can reach Suomenlinna island by the ferry (it's free, if you have a valid ticket to Tram or Subway or Helsinki Card).

name: Kauppatori
review_text: So far its amazing at night, we havent seen it open when we went there, but the surroundings are really gorgeous with the lights making it classic

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Loved the market here. Especially great for some sea food. Can be pricey like the rest if Helsinki but the food is good and lots to choose from. Nice view of the Cruise ships etc. Beware of the seagulls

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Great shopping place.  Yellow tents are food.  White tents are clothing and souvenirs.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
The food is good, but there are not enough places to sit.
Do not try to sit at another booth, the staff will kick you out (it is not written anywhere)

name: Kauppatori
review_text: It is a market where u can buy a lot of Souvenirs and you can eat diffrent Kind of food like for example fish. I was tgere in October so u defently need a bonnet

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Food hall but with an old retro nostalgic vibe. Lots of different food stalls.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Nice outdoor market that sells fresh fruit and vegetables, hot meals and handmade crafts. Watch out for the birds as they swoop down from no where to take food right out of your hands!

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Almost all hand made finnish food sell in this market .. mostly fish.. delicious.. met 2 Indonesian lady's sell fried fish. Hope you see this review. Apa kabar.. hope to visit Helsinki again

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Variety of food but overpriced fornwhat it is. Most stalls aell the same thing. Salmon soup. Salmon or meat with potatos.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Reindeer meatballs and Fried Vendace. Since I'm in a nordic country, the meatballs paired with the lingonberry sauce is no stranger to me as IKEA often has it.  What we do not have is reindeer meat which taste slightly gamier to me, I think I prefer the good old beef and pork mixed balls even though our Chinese cze char stall do serve deer meat so really just because its Santa's mode of transport doesn't mean its off limits as a staple meat here.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: great little area fresh seafood friendly people and souvenirs

name: Kauppatori
review_text: We liked this little market on the harbour with a mixture of food outlets and knic-naks. It cost me a fortune as she spied many things she liked.  Food was varied but good .Also many other spots near by ie. indoor market

name: Kauppatori
review_text: It's a nice walk through the lanes of Helsinki

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Nice stalls in the market area. Good souvenirs are eye catching things. Nice food shop for a full snack.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Many boat tour leaving from here,zoo,suomellina,dinner cruise
Try the stall cook food with meatballs/salmon set was great ,but beware of seagulls,they 'snatch' ur food from above!

name: Kauppatori
review_text: A must see for tourists and a lovely spot for locals. The view is great and the shopping supports small business

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Just a market with Street deep fried food! Finger food mainly!

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Awesome place for coffee and munkki.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Plenty fresh produce is available here. There are many tourists and tour bouts in this area. You can see two beautiful churches and the ferris wheel from this location. The hop-on hop-off busses stop near market square so it's a great place to go for a bite to eat and then go on a tour. The only downside is that there were many people there. It's not a bad thing but if you don't like massive crowds then this location is not for you. Having said that, it is very safe and clean.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: A bit disappointed about what I found. Just two places to eat bad quality and some local souvenir shops that were good.  If you plan to eat, go somewhere else, come here just for the souvenirs as you can support local businesses selling here

name: Kauppatori
review_text: It was fun seeing the different food but most vendors sold the exact same things.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Molto bello, caratteristico e pieno di cibi anche da assaggiare. Vale la pena fare un giro sia al mercato all'aperto che in quello interno, se siete in visita a Helsinki.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Mercato all’aperto sul porto di Helsinki .
Offre numerose bancarelle di verdura e frutta di produzione locale, alcune bancarelle di souvenir e una grande varietà di bancarelle destinate al street food.
Tutto da provare, certamente non economico ma simpatico e comodo durante il tour della città

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Gli stand di questo mercato sono molto belli e caratteristici, si trova dal cibo finlandese ai souvenir e anche frutta e verdura fresca del posto. Molto bello!

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Todos los youtubers hablan de visita imprescindible en Helsinki. Es más que imprescindible lógica porque está en un lugar imprescindible de la ciudad. Para un país que presume de modernidad es un mercado muy sencillo como de país del tercer mundo. Unos toldos, unas mesas difícil de limpiar. Autoservicio. Y pese a todo eso caro.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Restaurantes en el muelle donde se pueden comer productos locales, incluida la carne de reno, además de salmón y pescado frito. La comida es buena pero algo cara (adjunto fotos de precios) y has de buscar un lugar donde sentarte.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Wir haben sehr leckeren Fisch dort gegessen. Vorab durften wir probieren. Hinter oder neben den Verkaufsständen gibt es Bänke und Tische meist unter Zeltdächern. Natürlich nicht ganz billig. Leider haben die Stände fast identische Angebote. Ich würde mir mehr Vielfalt wünschen.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: 15 euro ya mega mix box yedim, karidesler güzeldi Kalamarlar biraz kuruydu, küçük balıklar oranın bölgesel balığı Çubuk Kraker gibi yeniyor 😁 bunun gibi başka tezgahlar da var Ayrıca meyve ve hediyelik eşya da satılıyor

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Marché agréable surtout fréquenté par des touristes comme nous je pense.
On y trouve des vendeurs de fruits et légumes, de l’artisanat mais également un certain nombre de stands où il est possible de se restaurer. Pour notre part, on a opté pour une assiette de friture avec salade, pommes de terre et sauce à l’aneth et une assiette mixte, identique à la précédente avec du saumon en plus.
Bien, assiettes bien garnies ! À faire une fois…

name: Kauppatori
review_text: 赫爾辛基集市廣場是遊客最多的廣場，來這走走逛逛體驗當地氣氛，絕對是個美好回憶。這裡的煎鮭魚好大一塊，看起來就垂涎三尺。喝個咖啡、品嚐小吃、買些紀念品、欣賞摩天輪、漫步碼頭等，就能讓人樂活一整天。

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Piccolo Mercato sul porticciolo dove poter comprare souvenir, gettarsi a capofitto nello street food locale o semplicemente passeggiare. Alle spalle delle bancarelle che propongono piatti tipici, ci si può fermare (altamente consigliato) per la degustazione degli stessi. Abbiamo assaggiato polpette di renna, hotdog di renna ed i coregoni fritti. Prezzi non da mercato, ma sapori autentici. Assolutamente da provare!

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Taze sebze ve meyvelerin satıldığı standların yanı sıra, aynı zamanda deniz ürünleri öncelikli olmak üzere bir çok hızlı pişir/ye seçeneklerin sunulduğu bir açık hava pazarı. Geyik eti denedim, çok lezzetliydi.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Un marché incontournable que nous avons bien apprécié avec des petits stands.De très jolis choses dont une personne qui fabrique des stylos et autres.Une halte s'impose, quelque soit l'heure pour déguster des petits poissons grillés et une assiette nordique.
Vraiment un régal qu'on ne peut que recommander.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: 超棒的市集，攤商非常多很好逛，可以買到當地的水果蔬菜及許多有當地特色的紀念品，衣物。可預留較多的時間，到此尋寶。

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Ein beliebter aber ruhiger Markt mit Aussicht auf die Schereninseln vor Helsinki welche früher Militärstellungen waren.Es gibt hier viele Ausflugsboote mit denen man dorthin fahren kann zu einem günstigen Preis
Am Markt kann man viele traditionelle  Sachen kaufen die in Handarbeit hergestellt wurden.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
思ったよりもコンパクトな感じで回りやすく、
色んなお土産があったり食事もできる。
可愛いカバンをお土産に購入し
フィンランド名物のサーモンスープやミートボールなども食べた。
フルーツなども販売している。
ヘルシンキに行ったら立ち寄ってみる事をおすすめします

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Soovitan läbi käia, turg on pigem turistidele suunatud suveniirid, kuid leidub ka kõike muud. Turu teises otsas on erinevat valmis toitu ja köögivilju.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Mercato Coperto di Helsinki. Purtroppo l'impressione è stata quella del classico posto solo per turisti... prezzi più alti rispetto al resto della città ed inoltre servizio inesistente in diversi banchi.
Orario di apertura dalle 8 alle 18.00.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Szép piac a kikötőben (Helsinki), büfékkel, zöldség-gyümölcs árusokkal (sok eperrel, mert ott még most érik), kézműves termékek, ajándék-áruk nagy választékával.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
La plaza del mercado de Helsinki se ubica en el puerto de la misma ciudad. Es un entorno donde la gente va a pasear y también a coger el ferry para ir a otros lugares.
Lo curioso de esta plaza es que está repleta de tiendecitas, no solamente de recuerdos si no también de comida local Finlandesa. La verdad es que no probé la comida finlandesa en ninguno de estos locales porque los mismos finlandeses me llevaban a restaurantes con buena comida.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Es un mercado de tenderetes situado en  un entorno muy lindo, en una explanada grande junto al puerto y a casas monumentales. Allí se vende comida, frutas, artesanía, ropas, recuerdos del país y se pasa un par de horas estupendas si el día está bueno. A las once de la mañana está en todo lo suyo.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Mycket trevlig upplevelse. Marknaden har både mat, frukt, grönsaker, blommor samt många olika finska hantverk.. Köpte stekt siklöja i ett av matstånden av otroligt trevlig personal. Tänk på att INTE äta mat utanför matstånden utan sitt ner under tak, måsarna kommer att attackera dig o maten.
Jag köpte även fina örhängen där fanns också mycket trevlig personal.
Presedentens palats ligger alldeles bakom marknadsplatsen.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
とても大きな規模のマーケットですね
お土産から、工芸品・野菜・果物・装飾品・レストランもあり
とても多くの人で賑わって居ました♪

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Qui ho mangiato sia il salmone che i mirtilli da un fruttivendolo. Entrambi molto buoni e di grande qualità. Stiamo parlando di luoghi aperti quindi è normale che ci siano in giro molti uccelli che mangiano ciò che cade o volino anche sui tavoli. Per il resto è un posto molto carino.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: O piata animată, cu mâncare, cu suveniruri, frumos loc, turistic.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: 헬싱키 바닷가 항구 근처에 위치한 전통 노천시장. 넓은 광장 옆쪽에 간이식 천막으로 제작된 부스가 나란히 세워져서 운영되고 있다. 매일 아침마다 텐트를 치고 밤에는 철거하는 형식인 것으로 보이는 다소 소박한 분위기의 장터이다. 핀란드어로 kauppa는 광장을, tori는 시장을 뜻하는데, 이 두개의 단어가 합쳐진 말이라고 한다. 과일, 채소, 생선과 육류 등 식료품 외에도 옷, 잡화  목공예품, 다양한 기념품 등을 파는 가게들이 있다. 여러가지 종류의 음식들로 판매해서 바로 주문해서 먹을수도 있다. 재미있게도 흰색천막은 상품을 판매하는 가게이고, 오렌지색 천막은 음식을 파는 곳으로 구분되어 있는것 같다. 가격대도 비싸지 않고 품질도 괜찮아 보여서 헬싱키 기념 옷을 몇벌 구입했다. 언제나 시장 구경은 재미있다.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: 주말과 평일에 다 방문해봤는데.. 역시 주말이 사람이 많아서 구경하기 쉽지 않았어요. 적당한 크기의 나무 컵을 구매했는데 만족합니다.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Ein muss beim Besuch in Helsinki. Es gibt sehr viele kulinarische Spezialitäten, auch die berühmte Fischsuppe mit Lachs und das Zimtgebäck. Auch der Markt am Hafen ist dahingehend empfehlenswert. 😋

name: Kauppatori
review_text: 로컬마켓이 참 재밌고 즐기기 좋았어요! 할머니가 직접 만들어 파시는 handmade cloth 냄비받침이 예뻐서 샀는데 너무 맘에 들었어요!! 냉장고 자석도 마많이 파니 모으시는 분들은 이곳으로 고고!!

name: Kauppatori
review_text: 마켓 뒤에 펼쳐지는 푸른 풍경이 엄청 멋있어요. 마켓 안에 간이식당도 있고 기념품 가게도 많아요

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Karışık tabak ve çorba söyledik. Balık çorbası çok sıcak ve güzeldi. Hamsi ve somon balığı enfes pişmişti, mutlaka denenmesi lazım. Hamsi hem az pişmiş ve sulu hem de kılçığı yok gibiydi, direkt yiyebilirsiniz. Abartmıyorum Türkiyede böylesini yemedim. Kalamarı iyi değildi.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
有麋鹿肉可以嚐嚐看
還有一些手工藝品
推薦來逛

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Los puestos exteriores en la plaza de mercado venden comida, artesanías, souvenirs y hasta ropa. Luego entra al local y en verdad que es preciosa su construcción, todos esos pequeños locales vendiendo productos artesanales y típicos de la región. Otros venden comida, cafe. Disfrutamos la visita al lugar. En esos mercados es donde uno realmente puede apreciar y degustar productos autóctonos.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: É um mercado a céu aberto no coração de Helsinki que oferece comidas típicas que ficam expostas ao sol a maior parte do tempo e preços para os turistas desavisados, de lá também partem os paaseios as ilhas finlândesas

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Helsingin kauppatorilta Etelärannasta  on merellinen näkymä merelle . Kauppakojuja useampia ,   joista löytyy niin ruokaa kuin matkamuistojakin . Turisteille se on varmaan mieluisa paikka tutustua.  Lokki lintuja siellä oli useampia yksilöitä  ,  joten kannattaa syödä ruokansa turvassa , ettei lokki pääse sitä nappaamaan . Jotenkin kesyntuntuisilta vaikuttivat . Samoin " ilmavaara " on ilmeinen   , kun lokit lentelevät torin yllä .

name: Kauppatori
review_text: フェリー乗り場から「エスプラナーディ公園」の方へ歩いて道の両脇が「マーケット広場 (カウッパトリ)」でした。民芸品や食べ物を売る屋台がたくさんありました。「ムルッカ」という「モトコクチマス」という小魚を揚げたものを売る屋台がいくつか並んでいて、試食もさせてくれました。クセも無くて美味しかったです。

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
農産物、クラフト小物、アクセサリー、服、そしてカフェやレストランなど、コンパクトながらいろいろ見られて楽しいです。
珍しい黄色いラズベリーが売っていました。
近くには様々な観光名所やアミューズメント施設があり、ふらっと立ち寄るにも良い場所にあると思います。

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Çok beğendim. Biz küçük balık, somon ızgara ve sebze ızgara yedik. Bayıldık

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Un lugar con encanto, sus puestos de fruros del bosque muy bonitos y las bayas buenísimas, vale la pena pagar por un par de cestitas. Y echarse un plato de salmón fresco a la plancha en los chiringuitos también vale la pena!

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Много лавок с местной едой, с ягодами и овощами, цены выше обычных, так как туристическое место, но можно поесть с видом на воду , в солнечный день особенно приятно

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Risteily Runeberg-aluksella edestakaisin Helsingistä Porvooseen oli hyvin  onnistunut. Henkilöknunta oli palvelu- luhenkistä ja ystävällistä. Yli 100-vuotias alus oli kaikin puolin mielenkiintoinen nähtävyys.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Der 2. Jahr, Frühling in Helsinki. Es war wieder wunderschön. Der Hafen, der Markt, die Zeltrestaurants am Markt und die Markthalle.
Keine Hektik, freundliche Mensche, Sonne und kühl. Das nordische Wetter ist klar, der Himmel richtig blau. Ich gerate ins schwärmen;-)

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
テントがあり、フィンランドのプレートの料理を座って食べることができます。
平日の１時頃に行きましたが、結構賑わっていました。
サーモンスープや、トナカイのソーセージ、クレープなどなどあります。
その他フルーツやキノコ、野菜も売っています。
フルーツの盛り合わせが売っていたので、購入しその場で食べましたが美味しかったです。

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Mile spędzony czas w tym miejscu,
Można zakupić warzywa,owoce oraz pamiątki

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Un mercato ricco di prodotti artigianali.
Dai guanti in pelle alle pantofole, ai lavori in lana cotta, all'abbigliamento.
Apprezzabili anche le saponette ricoperte da lana cotta.
Piccole bancarelle dove si può acquistare del salmone grigliato con bacche di ginepro, su un letto di verdure, veramente buono. Si può mangiare nel retro del banco, dove sono posizionati tavolini e sedie.
Da lì ci si può imbarcare per Suomenlinna.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: 食物味道中規中矩，價格比旁邊的老農貿市場划算。

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Magnífico mercado tradicional al aire libre para comprar recuerdos (carpas blancas) y para comer (carpas amarillas). Hay otro mercado más adelante cerrado, con comida algo más gourmet.
En las carpas se pueden comprar verduras, frutas, etc. Pero se puede comer allí también. Hay varios puestos con comidas que suelen ser salmón a la plancha deliciosamente especiado, patatas, verduras, pescaditos a la plancha, carne de reno y sopa de salmón, entre otros platos. Típico finlandés, todo delicioso, muy recomendable 😌

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Wirklich eine schöne Atmosphäre am Hafen. Schade dass die Stände auch am Wochenende bereits zeitig schließen.

Das Essen war super lecker. Die kleinen Fische (Maränen) muss man probiert haben.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Nel mercato coperto dove si può trovare da mangiare in tutte le salse

name: Kauppatori
review_text: 建議早點去，不過也沒什麼好逛的，賣吃的比較多。

name: Kauppatori
review_text: 가장 오래된 마켓 치고는 너무 깨끗하고 근사하다, 다만 판매 품목이 좀 단조롭다, 연어숩 과 각종 연어 스테이크 , 빵~

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Super místo na nábřeží. Spousta stánků se suvenýry i jídlem. Příjemné prostředí.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Bel.mercato di prodotti tipici e sou enir per turisti sul molo di Helsinki,prezzi un po'  "turistici",ma con diversi tipi di prodotti locali .finlandesi
Aperto tutti i goorno.nei mesi estivi.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Мало палаток з їжею,може доки рождества нема,не розумію.Дуже подобається місцезнаходження,з видом на воду,пором,колесо огляду.
Якщо пройти до церкви,через дорогу,то буде більш товарів,та палаток з традиційною їжею та сувенірами.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: 아기자기한 볼거리가 많아요. 데이트하기 좋은 곳이네요.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Eine kombinierte Bus-schiffstour gebucht. Sehr schöne Tour.  Zum Schluss ging das Boot kaputt.  1.30 Stunden auf ein Ersatzboot gewartet. Leider konnten wir due alte Markthalle nicht besuchen.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
La plaza del mercado se encuentra junto al muelle del puerto en el que se pueden coger los ferrys hacia islas de la ciudad, como Soumenlinna.

En el mercado hay puestos de fruta y verdura, principalmente, aunque también hay puestos de Souvenirs y de ropa.

Además también cuentan con distintos puestos de comida rápida en los que se ofrecen platos típicos del país como perritos de carne de reno.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Kevät ja torikauppiaat ovat saapuneet kauppatorille. Vesibusseissakin näyttää jo riittävän asiakkaita näin hyvällä säällä.

Näin kevättä kohti mennessä kun on aurinkoinen sää myyntikojut eli myyjät pikku hiljaa lisääntyvät taas torilla.
Jossain vaiheessa ei ollut kuin pari kahvinmyyntikojua.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Tempat yang menarik, open market, dan beberapa merchant bisa ditawar.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Keyifli tatli bir mekan. Dolasirken dinlenmek icin oturup bir seyler icebilirsiniz. Personel guler yuzlu. Bira guzel, corba soyledim soguk ve cok tuzluydu.begenmedim.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: direkt am Hafen, viele abwechslungsreiche Angebote süß und salzig, spannend anzuschauen sind die Möwen, die ständig auf der Jagd nach Eishörnchen sind

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Mercadito en el area de los mulles en Helsinki, varios lugares para comer, ventas de frutas, verduras y artesanias. Demasiado bonito y entretenido.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Marché de fruits et légumes avec  un food court proposant des choix variés notamment des produits de mer
"vendace" frites
Soupe au saumon
Chicken + french fries

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Mercato molto carino, dove servono piatti self service tipici finlandesi, bancarelle con prodotti finlandesi come souvenir, vestiti, creme ecc

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Wir waren im Zuge einer Kreuzfahrt hier. Wir haben extra weniger gefrühstückt um hier noch ein zweites Frühstück zu uns zu nehmen. Von den Preisen sehr angemessen. Sehr gemütlich und auch eine relativ grosse Auswahl.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Mercato piccolo ma carino!!! Si trova proprio sul porticciolo dove si prendono le barche per andare a Suomelinna o le altre isolette o fare il citytour. In questa piazza ci trovi dalle bancarella della frutta e dello street food a quello dei souvenir! Devo dire che ci sono tornata per pranzare per tutti e 2 i giorni che mi trovavo ad Helsinki. Sono stata molto felice (ed ancora ci penso) per l' ottima qualità dello street food! Ci sono varie bancarelle che propongono lo stesso menù altamente tipico del posto e devo dire che è tutto assolutamente buonissimo! Quindi se volete provare più pietanze, vi consiglio proprio di tornarci più volte se ne avete la possibilità. I piatti sono abbondanti, non proprio economici, ma d' altronde per il posto non credo sia molto..
un piatto di salmone con verdure costa solo 19 euro ed è squisito! Abbiamo assaggiato anche la renna e quei pesciolini fritti. Non prendete la birra tipica perché non ha niente a che vedere con la vera birra! Comunque dietro ad ogni bancarella ci sono dei tavolini liberi dove potersi sedere e gustare questo buonissimo cibo! 😋

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Somon çorbası o kadar güzel ki benden 5 yıldızı kapan şey o lezzet oldu. Onun dışında küçük şeker bir açık pazar. Özel değil ama görmek lazım.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: 東西很多，但賣的都差不多，不便宜

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
來的當天天氣很好！廣場上會有些小攤販、可能溫度很低、攤販數量不多，跟一位口愛的老奶奶買了她自己手作的圍巾，很喜歡。
廣場邊有渡輪可以到另外一座島上逛逛、蠻好的體驗、可以試試

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
La Plaza del Mercado de Helsinki, conocida como Kauppatori, es uno de los lugares más emblemáticos y vibrantes de la capital finlandesa. Situada junto al puerto, esta plaza es un punto de encuentro tanto para locales como para turistas, ofreciendo una experiencia auténtica de la vida diaria en Helsinki.

Kauppatori es famosa por sus coloridos puestos que venden una amplia variedad de productos frescos, desde frutas y verduras locales hasta pescado recién capturado del Báltico. Además, es el lugar ideal para probar delicias finlandesas, como el salmón ahumado, las bayas de temporada y los tradicionales "lihapiirakka" (empanadas de carne).

El entorno es espectacular, con vistas al mar, al Palacio Presidencial, y a la catedral Uspenski. En los días soleados, la plaza se llena de vida, convirtiéndose en un bullicioso mercado al aire libre, perfecto para pasear y disfrutar de la atmósfera única de Helsinki.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Un mercato turistico ma molto bello, si possono trovare bancarelle di ottimi cibi tipici e streetfood, oggetti artigianali in legno, lana, semplici souvenir. Io ho acquistato un bellissimo ciondolo da una bancarella di minerali, mi è stato creato "espresso" dalla pietra che ho scelto.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Ein schöner Markt. Tolle Stände mit Obst und Gemüse. Man kann da wunderbar essen und trinken. Natürlich gibt es da auch Souvenirstände. Sehr schöne Sachen dabei.
Die Sightseeingtouren per Boot beginnen auch dort. Alles richtig gut.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Geweldig, divers, heerlijk vers eten, gezellig

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Νόστιμα φαγητά της περιοχής
Αξίζει να το επισκεφθείτε
Εμείς φάγαμε κεφτεδάκια ταράνδου, σούπα σολωμου και πιάτο θαλασσινών

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Uno dei mercati più caratteristici di Helsinki, da non perdere in una visita alla città

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Mercato all'aperto molto carino. Le bancarelle offrono i prodotti tipici della Finlandia, dal food all'artigianato. E' possibile fermarsi a mangiare. Ottima la zuppa di salmone

name: Kauppatori
review_text: إذا كنت ترغب في تذوق الطعام الفنلندي التقليدي أو شراء الفنون والحرف المحلية ، فإن كوباتوري هو المكان المناسب للقيام بذلك. يقع أشهر أسواق هلسنكي في ساوث هاربور عند مدخل متنزه إسبلانادي. إنه مكان جيد لشراء جلود الرنة والمنحوتات الخشبية وتناول فطائر اللحم الفنلندية مثل lihapiirakka. يوفر السوق في الهواء الطلق إطلالات خلابة على ميناء هلسنكي وبحر البلطيق ، ويعد نقطة توقف جيدة للأشخاص الذين يستقلون العبارة إلى سومينلينا

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Nos gustó mucho el salmon con patatas y verduras y salsa de ajo. Súper barato para Helsinki. Recomendable.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Mercadito en la calle donde comer a precios relativamente asequibles y donde poder comprar souvenirs y productos de todo tipo

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Mercato molto particolare dove si può anche mangiare

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Hyviä muikkuja, mutta turistihinnat hirvittää. Ei puolisavolaisen kaaliin mahdu miten yksi muikku voi maksaa euron, kun idässä niitä saat kahdella kympillä muovikassillinen ja sukulaishinnoilla puolta kalliimmalla.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Helsinki sahilde özellikle deniz ürünleri ağırlıklı ama her türlü yiyecek içecek bulabileceğiniz bir açık hava pazar yeridir.
Satıcılar tadım yapmanıza izin de veriyorlar. Onların ikramları dışında ürünlere dokunmanızı, elinize almanızı hoş karşılamıyorlar.
Ben deniz ürünleri dahil sıkı bir etyemez olduğum için ürünler ve ortamın kokusu bana iyi gelmedi. (07 Ağustos 2023)

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Schöne Gegend um zu spazieren und etwas von Helsinki mitzunehmen, vor allem die Fahrt mit dem Schiff von A nach B oder C ist es schon wert über das eingefrorene Eis zu fahren. Leider waren nicht so viele Stände da, aber lag wohl an der Jahreszeit.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: سوق جميل يمكن شراء بعض الأشياء التذكاريه و الفواكه

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
位於港邊的市集
結合了古典與現代的氣息
早上不到十點就到，大多數的店家都還沒開張
大多以海鮮為主，也有咖啡店、中東、越南料理等
推薦可以去看看。

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Muchísima variedad de puestos y opción de acceder al mercado interior, por si llueve, con muchos más puestos a precios, mejores y más opciones de comida.

En nuestro caso, fuimos a un puesto típico con el que pudimos degustar una ensalada de salmón y un salmón al natural, luego fuimos a un puesto de Oriente medio en el que el tabulé estaba exquisito y, por último, un lugar en el que ofrecía panales de miel y varias opciones de pescado, que también estaba muy bien. Un lugar turístico, pero que merece la pena ir si estás por el centro de Helsinki.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Kunhan nyt kiertelin ja muistelin vuotta 1980 kun itse olin vähän aikaa torimyyjänä. Kauppa kävi huonosti joten teimme vaihtokauppaa kojunaapurin kanssa. Saamani villasukat ovat edelleen käytössä. ☀️

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Helsinkiläisille tuttu rakas paikka. Keskellä kaikkee, meri, turistiristeilyt, Suomenlinnaan laivat + lähi saariin lähtevät. Iki ihana vaha Kauppatori jossa monipuoliset tarjonnat kahvilat, kalakojut, juustokojut, monet leivonnaiset. Wc-tilat joita voisin morttii, kun ovat niin pienet ja vain kaksi. Turistit jouto jonottaa jokseenkin kauan. Mutta johtunee tilan rakenteista saada paremmaksi. Kauppatori lisäksi kaikkineen käsitöineen ja ruokapisteineen. Upea Suurkirkko ja Usbeskin katetraali myös aivan lähellä käpästä. Kuvvii ei tullunna otettuu. Unohtamatta entisöityy Havis Amandaa.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: 炸魚還可以，但是看起來像是炸魷魚圈的東西居然是麵粉做的簡直強盜行為，煎蝦子很鹹，總之不要對他有什麼期望，這樣一小盤要15€，無語

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Lugar con puestecitos de artesanía, ropa y complementos. También se pueden comprar souvenirs y comida típica caliente, muy rica la verdad. Para ser diciembre, habia bastante puesto decente y siempre pidiéndote resguardar en los puestos de comida, que estaban aclimatados

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
廣場在港口邊。廣場賣很多熟食、蔬果、還有紀念品。如果還沒有買到芬蘭的紀念品的，可以在這裡一站購足，呵呵。

天氣好的時候，到處都是在廣場上曬太陽的人。很好逛的地方。

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Mercatini dove mangiare piatti tipici e acquistare gadget e abbigliamento.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Mercatino all'aperto strepitoso per lo street food e lo shopping dei souvenirs. Consiglio di mangiare il salmone (cercate lo stand che lo cuoce interamente) e le patate...deliziosi. In merito ai souvenirs, ci sono bancarelle specializzate in prodotti artigianali fatti in legno (animali a calamita etc), davvero originali

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Mercato caratteristico di Helsinki, vi è sia una parte all'aperto che una molto sugestiva al chiuso. Possibilità di acquistare ogni cibo caratteristico finlandese e non solo. Ottimo anche per una pausa pranzo o per una cena

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Kasviksia, juureksia, marjoja ja hedelmiä, matkamuistoja, ruokaa ja kahvia. Rannasta lautat Suomenlinnaan ja korkeasaareen.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: 逛逛走走停停！又是搭船處！

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Ihana aurinkoinen aamu meren rannalla.
Kahvi oli hyvää ja palvelu erinomaista.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Un luogo imperdibile di Helsinki. Tanti ambulanti e tanti prodotti locali specie di frutta verdura. Fragole e ribes i più buoni mai mangiati. Caratteristico e sounvenir abbastanza convenienti rispetto alla media. Se si vuole gustare street food questo è il posto ideale

name: Kauppatori
review_text: 市集的物品都還算不錯，正常芬蘭價；但這區及周圍有一堆小偷，要非常注意身上的物品，稍有分心，包包將被打開和搜刮

name: Kauppatori
review_text: 個人認為這個地方逛逛便好了，不要在這兒吃東西，因爲又貴又不好吃。隔鄰的「老農貿市場」也是個專做遊客生意的地方，參觀一下，影相打卡無妨，但不要光顧。我們吃了魚子醬及當地的特色甜品，完全不好吃，仲要好貴，做了豬仔！

name: Kauppatori
review_text: 很热闹的市场，可以吃点本地的白鲑鱼

name: Kauppatori
review_text: 市集很熱鬧、遊人眾多、鄰近風景很美'有地道美味熟食、但消費挺貴

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Mercato all'aperto in cui in cui si trova principalmente street food finlandese e souvenir, non c'è molta scelta, tutte le bancarelle propongono gli stessi prodotti a ripetizione. Consigliato per chi si trova in zona e vuole mangiare un piatto veloce senza troppe pretese.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Mercado junto al Puerto de Helsinki. En Otoño el clima es muy frío y no vimos la feria afuera solo los puestos adentro del local. Variedad de restarantes de comida típica. Mucho Salmón y comida marina.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Market Square (Piața Centrală) din Helsinki este un paradis culinar pentru cei pasionați de mâncare și aventură gastronomică. Acest târg vibrant, situat în inima orașului, oferă o experiență captivantă pentru toți gurmanzii. Când pășești în piață, aroma proaspătă a fructelor, legumelor și fructelor de mare proaspăt pescuite îți îmbie simțurile.

Vizitatorii pot savura bucate tradiționale finlandeze precum salmonul afumat și renumitul karjalanpiirakka (plăcintă kareliană) în variante autentice, pregătite cu măiestrie de comercianții locali. Standurile abundă în delicii locale, cum ar fi marinatele nordice, fructele de pădure sălbatice și brânzeturile artizanale.

Un punct culminant este reprezentat de "Kalakukko", un tort de pește finlandez îmbinat cu carne de porc, încorporat într-o crustă de aluat. Nu lipsesc nici preparatele cu somon proaspăt, gătite în stiluri variate, de la grătar la afumare.

Cu toate acestea, Market Square nu este doar despre mâncare, ci și despre atmosferă. Muzicanții stradali și mirosurile seducătoare creează o ambianță efervescentă. Cu numeroasele mese în aer liber, poți savura cu ușurință bucatele achiziționate și te poți bucura de priveliștea spre portul aglomerat.

În concluzie, Market Square din Helsinki este un regat al deliciilor finlandeze și al aromei autentice. Este un must-see pentru orice gurmand care dorește să experimenteze bucătăria și cultura locală într-un cadru pitoresc și plin de viață.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Mercato piccolo e molto turistico. Gli stand gastronomici non sono male

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Szuperjó hely! Eredetileg óriáskererekezni mentünk, de utána muszáj volt megnéznünk a kikötő többi részét is. Kipróbáltuk a rénszarvas mix tálat, illetve némi tenger gyümölcseit. Itt vettük meg az otthoniaknak szánt ajándék hűtòmágneseket is. A lámák nagyon jófejek voltak, bár nem tudom, ők is eladóak-e. :)

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
La plaza del Mercado de Helsinki​ es una céntrica plaza llena de puestos de artesanía, ropa, flores, comida, y souvenires.

Al lado del puerto y céntrica. Puedes coger el ferry o ir al antigup mercado de Helsinki dónde poder comer platos típicos o comprar carne de oso, reno y alce.
Hay puestos de comida dónde te preparan hamburguesas de reno, o salmón en el momento.
Parada obligada para sentir que estás haciendo algo típico de allí.
La carne de reno es bastante seca. Pero pruebas una gastronomía diferente.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
可愛小市集
有吃有買

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Jedno z nielicznych miejsc w Helsinkach, gdzie można zjeść dobre jedzenie w przystępnej cenie. Kremowa zupa rybna z łososiem (11 Euro), mięsne pulpeciki z opiekanymi ziemniakami i surówka (10 Euro), mięso z renifera z dodatkami (20 Euro). Codziennie można spróbować czegoś innego.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
戶外的市集，有熟食、點心、水果及一些手工藝品。
市集旁也有不少歷史建築及遊客中心，
能從市集旁的碼頭搭船去芬蘭堡。

很多海鷗！

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Hieno tori meren ääressä. Aina mukava tunnelma.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Hautaamassa äitiä mereen 😭 Ihana palvelu hautausveneessä. Kauppatorin muikut, ja ihan ehdoton lohikeitto olivat maukkaita. Ihmisvilinää. Kauniita muistoja lapsuudesta tähän päivään. Helsinki on mun ensimmäinen kotikylä. En muuttaisi takaisin, liian paljon ihmisiä...

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Un grand marché pour découvrir les produits locaux, tant alimentaires que habits ou souvenirs.
Les vendeurs sont ouverts au dialogue, partagent aisément leur langue pour autant que vous essayez.
Une expérience à tenter.
Attention aux mouettes qui n'hésitent pas à se poser sur votre tête pour piquer un morceau ;-)

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Antico mercato di helsinki,  oggi occupato dal negozietti di fastfood,

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Un ottimo posto dove mangiare piatti a base di pesce azzurro e salmone. Io ho gustato un mix e l'ho trovato molto buono. I prezzi vanno dai 10 euro sino a 18 euro.

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
Maknadstorg, alltid trevlig stämning när man kommer ner här.
Luktar gott från alla mat tälten, ser fräscht ut.
Alltid nått på gång på detta stället, både sommartid och vintertid.
Ligger fantastiskt till intill vattnet, med både Tallink och Viking färjorna i närheten.

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Ganz toller Platz. Auf jeden Fall die Fischsuppe probieren!!

name: Kauppatori
review_text:
雖然營業時間標示的很早，但太早來大多的攤販仍在準備，個人感覺週日的攤販數量也比較少，建議安排平日前往。
各類攤販有販售水果、鮭魚餐點、紀念品等等的。

name: Kauppatori
review_text: Me encantó pasear por sus puestecitos de fruta, comida típica y souvenirs, ver pasear a la gente y el puerto.

name: Kauppatori
